Pope Francis has condemned the attack on St Francis Catholic Church in Owo LGA of Ondo state. The Nation reports gunmen attacked the church on Sunday, killing many worshippers and injuring several people. Gunmen were said to have thrown an improvised explosive device before they started shooting sporadically.   Ikpeazu gives quit notice to herders, others in Abia forests     Eagles to give 100  percent against Leone Stars , says Aribo     Power must shift to south, Akeredolu insists   The 85-year-old cleric expressed his condolences to the victims’ families. He said: “I was deeply saddened to learn of the horrific attack at Saint Francis church in Owo in #Nigeria. “#PrayTogether for all those affected by this act of unspeakable violence and for the conversion of those blinded by hatred and violence.”